  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protection, Assistance and Durable Solutions for People with Disabilities in North-East Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving shelter, essential household item, and early recovery assistance to internally displaced persons, returnees and host communities in Bama. This UNHCR project focuses specifically on assisting persons with disabilities by: providing livelihood opportunities including through cash transfers; distributing shelter and essential household item kits; delivering assistive devices such as orthotics, wheelchairs, hearing aids and other mobility devices; and equipping households with fuel-efficient stoves. The project provides life-saving assistance to 850 persons with disabilities, including 200 women, 190 men, and 460 children.</narrative>
  </description>
